@Andrzej I agree with the others, Ms. is not actually an abbreviation. It's pronounced Mizz, and it goes way back in southern US dialect, but I think the period is at the end because other American titles have periods at the end. It would look weird to say Mr. Jones and Ms Smith.

Swiss Ms. is also a play on a brand of instant hot cocoa mix called Swiss Miss.

All that said, I tried for some time to fit an abbreviation for fraulein in there. Then reread the clue and thought "oh it's just FRAU, you dope." Fraulein would rather be the opposite of the meaning behind Ms.

